  "text": "The LLVM optimization pass pipeline is orchestrated through a coordinated system of components:\n\n1. **PassBuilder Class** (llvm/include/llvm/Passes/PassBuilder.h, llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilder.cpp): This is the main orchestrator class that constructs optimization pipelines. The key method is `buildModuleOptimizationPipeline()` defined at line 1478-1479 in PassBuilderPipelines.cpp, which builds the default O2 optimization pipeline for modules. This method returns a ModulePassManager containing all the passes that make up the optimization pipeline.\n\n2. **PassManager Template Class** (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h, lines 159-226): This is the core pass execution engine. It's a template class defined as `template<typename IRUnitT, typename AnalysisManagerT = AnalysisManager<IRUnitT>, typename... ExtraArgTs> class PassManager`. The template is specialized for Module and Function units via typedefs: ModulePassManager (line 238) and FunctionPassManager (line 247). It implements the run() method (line 190-191) which executes all passes in sequence over the IR unit.\n\n3. **PassBuilderPipelines** (llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilderPipelines.cpp): This file implements the actual pipeline construction logic, particularly the `buildModuleOptimizationPipeline()` method. This function assembles the complete pipeline of function passes (OptimizePM) and module passes that work together to optimize code. It makes decisions based on optimization level and adds passes like loop unrolling, vectorization, and dead store elimination in the appropriate order.\n\n4. **PassRegistry.def** (llvm/lib/Passes/PassRegistry.def): This central registry file defines all built-in standard passes using macro invocations. Passes are registered with macros like MODULE_PASS, FUNCTION_PASS, etc. Each pass registration includes the string name used in textual pipelines and the instantiation code. The file is #include'd multiple times in PassBuilder.cpp to support different registration contexts.\n\n5. **DeadStoreElimination Pass** - A concrete example of a registered optimization pass:\n   - Header (llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Scalar/DeadStoreElimination.h): Defines the `DSEPass` class which inherits from `PassInfoMixin<DSEPass>` and implements `PreservedAnalyses run(Function &F, FunctionAnalysisManager &FAM)`.\n   - Implementation (llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/DeadStoreElimination.cpp): Contains the actual algorithm that eliminates redundant stores using MemorySSA.\n   - Registration (llvm/lib/Passes/PassRegistry.def, line 433): `FUNCTION_PASS(\"dse\", DSEPass())` registers the pass so it can be instantiated by PassBuilder.\n\nThe execution flow is: PassBuilder::buildModuleOptimizationPipeline() constructs a ModulePassManager, which contains FunctionPassManagers filled with individual passes (like DSEPass). When run() is invoked, the PassManager executes each pass in sequence, propagating analysis results and invalidating them as needed."
}

